README for medicalterms
=======================

The goal of this package is to create specialized dictionaries for medical
terms used in various languages. Those dictionaries can be used easily with
aspell, an advanced spellchecker.

As of now, German is the only supported language. If you'd like to contribute
to the development of the package medicalterms, please contact me. You can
find the latest version on <http://gna.org/projects/medicalterms/>.


Configuration options
=====================

The configure script currently accepts the following option:

--enable-orthography=<new|old|both>

You can use this option to select which spelling variant should be included
in the dictionary. "old" is the old orthography, "new" the variant as of
August 1, 1998, and "both" will include both spellings. The configuration
defaults to "new".


Access to the source code repository
====================================

This project uses GNU arch as its revision control system. More
specifically, the bazaar implementation is used as a frontend. You can
check out the latest development sources with the following commands:

$ baz register-archive medicalterms-dev@gna.org http://arch.gna.org/medicalterms
$ baz get medicalterms-dev@gna.org/medicalterms--main--1.0 medicalterms

As this is a signed archive, you might want to tell baz how to verify the
signatures found in the archive. Please consult the baz manual on how to do
this. If you don't configure baz to verify signed archives, you can still
check out the sources -- baz will only warn you about not having verified
the signatures.

Please note that there are no automatically generated files included. This
means that you need automake (> 1.6.3) and autoconf (> 2.59) to build those
files yourself. You can use the following commands:

$ aclocal
$ baz changelog > ChangeLog
$ automake --add-missing
$ autoconf

Now you can start hacking away -- don't forget to send your patches to me!


